  "text": "The cell envelope samples were made by sonicating bacteria (10 9 cells/ml) in PBS on ice with 2.5 mM ethylene diamine tetra-acetic acid (EDTA). The remaining cells were pelleted, and the supernatants were centrifuged further. The cell envelopes in the supernatants were pelleted and suspended in PBS and SDS-PAGE loading buffer. Whole-cell samples were made by boiling the bacteria (10 9 cells/ml) with SDS-PAGE loading buffer, and the samples were loaded into a 12% (wt/vol) SDS-PAGE gel, electrophoresed, and transferred onto a nitrocellulose membrane. The proteins were detected with a mixture of anti-His 6 -Pla antiserum, antipeptide sera against Pla loops 3 and 5 [CITATION_1] , and anti-His 6 -Epo antiserum (1:1000). The detection was done with alkalinephosphatase-conjugated anti-rabbit immunoglobulin G (IgG; Dako) and phosphatase substrate.",
